column5: Thinking of trying for my first time. Have never been there. Curious about launching. Is there a good place? Hall's cottages perhaps? Just going for the day and am an experienced muskie fisherman. Need to fish more "Bay water".  Thanks,  Dave
You could try Bayview Marina.  I used to launch my boat there years ago.
Launch at Village Marina at the end of Honey Harbour Rd.. Great launch and only $20.00.. We use it and have been using it for the past 20 years..
Thanks for the info guys. Appreciate it very much.
I launch at village marine,  good launch. Have never caught or seen a musky yet in the honey harbour area but have heard their there. Good luck!
I've seen a few muskies when bass fishing, but not with any sort of frequency.  +1 for Village Marine.
